sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as Consuming app
    participant Storage as AppEncryptionStorage
    participant Core as enclaveapp-core traits/types
    participant Backend as Selected backend
    participant HSM as Secure Enclave / TPM / keyring
    participant Disk as App cache file

    App->>Storage: create_encryption_storage(StorageConfig)
    Storage->>Storage: detect platform and initialize backend
    Storage->>Backend: ensure encryption key exists
    Backend->>HSM: create or load P-256 encryption key
    Backend-->>Storage: public key / metadata ready

    App->>Storage: encrypt(plaintext secret)
    Storage->>Core: validate label and access policy
    Storage->>Backend: encrypt(label, plaintext)
    Backend->>HSM: use P-256 ECDH key agreement
    Backend-->>Storage: ECIES ciphertext
    Storage-->>App: ciphertext bytes
    App->>Disk: write app-specific cache format

    App->>Disk: read ciphertext
    App->>Storage: decrypt(ciphertext)
    Storage->>Backend: decrypt(label, ciphertext)
    Backend->>HSM: private-key operation / unwrap
    HSM-->>Backend: shared-secret operation result
    Backend-->>Storage: plaintext
    Storage-->>App: plaintext secret

    Note over App,Disk: libenclaveapp does not define app domain semantics for cached payloads.

